      "title": "Enlace metálico"
    },
    {
      "description": "Explica enlaces por superposición de orbitales atómicos de valencia y emparejamiento de electrones.",
      "title": "Teoría del enlace de valencia"
    },
    {
      "description": "Mezcla de orbitales s y p para formar dos orbitales híbridos lineales utilizados en enlaces.",
      "title": "Hibridación sp"
    },
    {
      "description": "Mezcla de orbitales s y p para formar tres orbitales híbridos en geometría triangular plana.",
      "title": "Hibridación sp2"
    },
    {
      "description": "Mezcla de orbitales s y tres p para formar cuatro orbitales híbridos en geometría tetraédrica.",
      "title": "Hibridación sp3"
    },
    {
      "description": "Expansión del octeto mediante mezcla de s, p y d para formar orbitales híbridos en especies con más de ocho electrones.",
      "title": "Hibridación sp3d"
    },
    {
      "description": "Combinación de orbitales atómicos para formar orbitales moleculares que describen enlaces y estructuras.",
      "title": "Orbitales moleculares"
    },
    {
      "description": "Enlace sigma: solapamiento frontal de orbitales que genera la unión principal en enlaces simples.",
      "title": "Enlaces σ"
    },
    {
      "description": "Enlace pi: solapamiento lateral de orbitales p que acompaña a enlaces dobles o triples.",
      "title": "Enlaces π"
    },
    {
      "description": "Distribución desigual de cargas en una molécula debido a diferencias de electronegatividad.",
      "title": "Polaridad molecular"
    },
    {
      "description": "Capacidad de un átomo para atraer electrones compartidos hacia sí.",
      "title": "Electronegatividad"
    },
    {
      "description": "Medida de la polaridad de una molécula; vector que señala desde el polo negativo hacia el positivo.",
      "title": "Momento dipolar"
    },
    {
      "description": "Teoría de la repulsión de pares de electrones para predecir la geometría alrededor de un átomo central.",
      "title": "VSEPR"
    },
    {
      "description": "Disposición espacial de átomos en una molécula basada en los pares enlazantes y no enlazantes.",
      "title": "Geometría molecular"
    },
    {
      "description": "Pares de electrones no enlazantes en un átomo central que influyen en la geometría y la polaridad.",
      "title": "Pares solitarios"
    }
  ]
}

{
  "lessons": [
    {
      "description": "Y is modeled as a linear combination of regressors plus an error term: Y = Xβ + ε.",
      "title": "Linear Regression Model"
    },
    {
      "description": "Estimate β̂ by minimizing the sum of squared residuals: SSE = e'e.",
      "title": "OLS Objective: Minimize SSE"
    },
    {
      "description": "β̂ = (X'X)^{-1}X'Y, assuming X has full column rank.",
      "title": "OLS Estimator Formula"
    },
    {
      "description": "Fitted values Ŷ = Xβ̂ and residuals e = Y − Ŷ.",
      "title": "Fitted Values and Residuals"
    },
    {
      "description": "OLS residuals are orthogonal to every column of X, i.e., X'e = 0.",
      "title": "Residuals Orthogonal to Regressors"
    },
    {
      "description": "Model is linear in β; coefficients appear as additive weights on regressors.",
      "title": "Linearity in Parameters"
    },
    {
      "description": "ε captures all factors not explained by X in the model.",
      "title": "Error Term Definition"
    },
    {
      "description": "E[ε|X] = 0: errors have zero mean conditional on the regressors.",
      "title": "Zero Conditional Mean"
    },
    {
      "description": "X must have full column rank; no exact linear dependence among regressors.",
      "title": "No Perfect Multicollinearity"
    },
    {
      "description": "Cov(ε, X) = 0, ensuring regressors are not correlated with the error.",
      "title": "Exogeneity of Regressors"
    },
    {
      "description": "Var(ε|X) = σ^2, constant variance of errors across observations.",
      "title": "Homoscedasticity"
    },
    {
      "description": "Errors are uncorrelated across observations (ε_i independent of ε_j for i ≠ j).",
      "title": "No Autocorrelation"
    },
    {
      "description": "Errors are normally distributed (useful for small-sample inference).",
      "title": "Normality of Errors"
    },
    {
      "description": "Parameters are identifiable when a unique β corresponds to the observed distribution of Y given X.",
      "title": "Identification in Linear Models"
    },
    {
      "description": "Under classical assumptions, OLS is the Best Linear Unbiased Estimator.",
      "title": "Gauss–Markov: BLUE"
    },
    {
      "description": "Var(β̂) = σ^2 (X'X)^{-1}, describing precision of coefficient estimates.",
      "title": "Variance of β̂"
    },
    {
      "description": "Use s^2 = SSE/(n − k) to estimate the error variance when fitting the model.",
      "title": "Estimating σ^2"
    },
    {
      "description": "Residual degrees of freedom: n − k.",
      "title": "Degrees of Freedom for Error"
    },
    {
      "description": "t = (β̂_j − β_j0)/SE(β̂_j) tests a single coefficient against a null value.",
      "title": "t-Statistic for a Coefficient"
    },
    {
      "description": "Tests if a group of coefficients is jointly zero using the F statistic.",
      "title": "F-Statistic for Joint Significance"
    },
    {
      "description": "H0: a coefficient equals a specified value (e.g., β_j = β_j0).",
      "title": "Null Hypothesis"
    },
    {
      "description": "H1: a coefficient differs from the null value (e.g., β_j ≠ β_j0).",
      "title": "Alternative Hypothesis"
    },
    {
      "description": "P-value is the probability of observing a statistic as extreme as the one observed under H0.",
      "title": "P-Value Interpretation"
    },
    {
      "description": "Interval estimate around β̂_j using its standard error.",
      "title": "Confidence Interval for a Coefficient"
    },
    {
      "description": "α defines the threshold for rejecting H0 in hypothesis tests.",
      "title": "Significance Level"
    },
    {
      "description": "Type I: falsely rejecting a true H0; Type II: failing to reject a false H0.",
      "title": "Type I and Type II Errors"
    },
    {
      "description": "Probability of correctly rejecting H0 when the alternative is true.",
      "title": "Power of a Test"
    },
    {
      "description": "Examine residuals to detect misspecification or model inadequacy.",
      "title": "Residuals Analysis"
    },
    {
      "description": "Assess whether residuals deviate from normality by plotting quantiles.",
      "title": "Normal Q-Q Plot of Residuals"
    },
    {
      "description": "Breusch-Pagan tests for heteroskedasticity in the regression residuals.",
      "title": "Breusch-Pagan Test"
    },
    {
      "description": "A robust, nonparametric test for heteroskedasticity without assuming a form.",
      "title": "White Test for Heteroskedasticity"
    },
    {
      "description": "Tests for autocorrelation in residuals, especially in time series data.",
      "title": "Durbin-Watson Statistic"
    },
    {
      "description": "Detect misspecification and incorrect functional form by adding powers of fitted values.",
      "title": "Ramsey RESET Test"
    },
    {
      "description": "VIF quantifies multicollinearity risk among regressors.",
      "title": "Variance Inflation Factor"
    },
    {
      "description": "Adjust standard errors to be valid under heteroskedasticity or certain misspecifications.",
      "title": "Robust Standard Errors"
    },
    {
      "description": "Identify observations that unduly affect the regression results.",
      "title": "Influential Observations: Cook's Distance"
    },
    {
      "description": "High-leverage points can disproportionately affect the fit.",
      "title": "Leverage and Influence"
    },
    {
      "description": "Plot actual vs. fitted values to visually assess goodness of fit.",
      "title": "Model Fit Visualization"
    },
    {
      "description": "Use information criteria to compare competing models.",
      "title": "AIC and BIC for Model Comparison"
    },
    {
      "description": "Omitted variables or wrong functional form bias coefficients and inferences.",
      "title": "Misspecification Implications"
    }
  ]
}

