{
  "lessons": [
    {
      "description": "How a subordinate clause is linked to the main clause using the connector que.",
      "title": "Que introduces a noun clause"
    },
    {
      "description": "Form the present subjunctive endings for -AR verbs (e.g., hablar: hable, hables, hable...).",
      "title": "Present subjunctive endings for -AR verbs"
    },
    {
      "description": "Form the present subjunctive endings for -ER and -IR verbs (e.g., comer: coma, comas, coma...).",
      "title": "Present subjunctive endings for -ER/-IR verbs"
    },
    {
      "description": "Conjugation of estar in the present subjunctive: esté, estés, esté, estemos, estéis, estén.",
      "title": "Estar in the present subjunctive"
    },
    {
      "description": "Conjugation of ir in the present subjunctive: vaya, vayas, vaya, vayamos, vayáis, vayan.",
      "title": "Ir in the present subjunctive"
    },
    {
      "description": "Key irregulars in the present subjunctive: ser → sea, estar → esté.",
      "title": "Ser vs. estar in the subjunctive forms"
    },
    {
      "description": "Use hacer que to express causing someone to do something; the following clause uses the subjunctive.",
      "title": "Hacer que: influence through causation"
    },
    {
      "description": "Expresses obligation with que; the subordinate clause takes the subjunctive.",
      "title": "Obligar a que: obligation to cause action"
    },
    {
      "description": "Prohibition in the main clause triggers a subjunctive in the following clause.",
      "title": "Prohibir que: prohibition expressed"
    },
    {
      "description": "Express permission with que; the noun clause uses the subjunctive.",
      "title": "Permitir que: giving permission"
    },
    {
      "description": "Offer a recommendation that someone do something; the subordinate clause is subjunctive.",
      "title": "Recomendar que: formal recommendation"
    },
    {
      "description": "Advice that something should happen; use subjunctive in the noun clause.",
      "title": "Aconsejar que: giving advice"
    },
    {
      "description": "Ask that someone do something; the subordinate clause uses the subjunctive.",
      "title": "Pedir que: direct request"
    },
    {
      "description": "Desire that something occurs; triggers the subjunctive in the noun clause.",
      "title": "Desear que: express desire"
    },
    {
      "description": "Want that someone do something; the subordinate clause uses the subjunctive.",
      "title": "Querer que: volition and desire"
    },
    {
      "description": "Hope that something happens; the following clause is in subjunctive.",
      "title": "Esperar que: hope and expectation"
    },
    {
      "description": "Prefer that something occur; use the subjunctive in the noun clause.",
      "title": "Preferir que: preference expressed"
    },
    {
      "description": "Ojalá expresses a strong wish and triggers the present subjunctive in the subordinate clause.",
      "title": "Ojalá que: strong wish"
    },
    {
      "description": "Doubt about an action or event; use the subjunctive in the noun clause.",
      "title": "Dudar que: express doubt"
    },
    {
      "description": "Doubt or disbelief with no creer; the subordinate clause takes the subjunctive.",
      "title": "No creer que: disbelief and doubt"
    },
    {
      "description": "Not being sure that something is true; subjunctive in the noun clause.",
